        <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is a content automation platform?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A content automation platform owns the workflow end-to-end — ideation, drafting, optimization, publishing, and reporting. It is different from a writing tool (which generates) or a CMS (which stores). Platforms automate the loop; tools automate one step.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Which content automation platform is best for small businesses?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>theStacc is the best fit for small businesses under $5M revenue — Content SEO at $99/mo handles the full SEO publishing loop. HubSpot Content Hub is best for sales-led teams that already use HubSpot CRM. Letterdrop is best for editorial-led content ops.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How much do content automation platforms cost in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Self-serve platforms start at $39/mo (Narrato, Byword). Mid-market platforms cost $99–$500/mo (theStacc, Jasper, Letterdrop, CoSchedule). Enterprise platforms (HubSpot Content Hub, Contently) start at $890–$5,000+/mo with annual contracts.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between content automation and a CMS?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A CMS (WordPress, Webflow, Ghost) stores and publishes the content you create. A content automation platform creates the content and pushes it to your CMS. The CMS is the destination — the platform is the workflow.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Do content automation platforms replace writers?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>They replace 60–80% of drafting time. Editorial review, brand voice tuning, and strategic content still need a human. Teams that go full-AI without review ship lower quality and rank worse. The right model is platform-drafts plus human-edits.</p></div></div>
          </div>
